<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 16:00 GMT, May 17 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Indian Prime Minister Atal Vajpayee assured
the international community Sunday that his country would never
use its nuclear program as a "weapon of aggression."
</P>
<P>
He repeated his position that India could not succumb to
pressures to sign what he called discriminatory treaties like the
Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty and the non-proliferation treaties
which he said have utterly failed to bring about any progress in
global nuclear disarmament. (India-Vajpayee-Nuclear Weapons)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistani Foreign Secretary Shamshad Ahmad has
left for Beijing for consultations with Chinese leaders on the
recent developments in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
As a part of the process of regular consultations, Foreign
Secretary Ahmad left for Beijing this morning, the Pakistani
Foreign Office said in a press release
Sunday. (Pakistan-China-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM - Two Palestinians were reportedly injured in the
West Bank town of Hebron Sunday as clashes between the
Palestinians and Israeli soldiers entered its fourth day.
</P>
<P>
The clashes erupted when Palestinians threw firebombs and
stones at Israeli soldiers, who responded with rubber bullets,
Israel Radio reported. (Israel-Palestinian-Clashes)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistan has firmly denied reports that it
conducted a nuclear test Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
"This is a motivated rumor," said a Foreign Office spokesman in
a one-sentence statement Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The statement came after a Western news agency reported earlier
Sunday that German Chancellor Helmut Kohl, "quoting reliable
information," said in Birmingham, England, that Pakistan had
carried out a nuclear test. (Pakistan-Denial-Nuclear Test-1stadd)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
COLOMBO -- The mayor of Sri Lanka's northern Jaffna town,
Sarojini Yogeswaran, was shot dead by a lone gunman on Sunday,
informed sources here said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said Yogeswaran, 60, was attacked at her home in
Jaffna city, about 260 kilometers from Colombo.
</P>
<P>
Yogeswaran, a member of the Tamil United Liberation Front
(TULF), was sworn in last March as the first Mayor of former
Tamil rebel northern strong-hold Jaffna since 1984. (Sri
Lanka-Mayor-1stlead) 
</P>
</TEXT>
