<HEADLINE> Kazibwe Still Being Uganda's Vice-President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The State House of Uganda
announced that Specioza Wandira Kazibwe remains the vice
president of Uganda, putting to rest mounting speculation that
she was dropped out in the latest cabinet reshuffle by President
Yoweri Museveni.
</P>
<P>
A brief statement from the State House said Saturday night:
"There has been some confusion arising out of the re-organization
of ministries regarding the position of the vice president. This
is to clarify that Specioza W.N. Kazibwe remains vice president
of the country."
</P>
<P>
"It was thought superfluous to state this (that Kazibwe was
still vice president) in the document," the statement added.
</P>
<P>
It said that the predient's office was prompted into making
the statement because of the confusion Friday night's
announcement created.
</P>
<P>
Friday's announcement only named Kazibwe as Minister of
Agriculture, Animal Industry and Fisheries.
</P>
<P>
Hope Kivengere, the Press Secretary to the President, was
quoted by Sunday's Monitor newspaper as saying that the omission
on the reshuffle list might have been a typographical oversight.
</P>
<P>
Museveni announced a surprise cabinet reshuffle list Friday
night, with the name of Kazibwe only mentioned as the
Agricultural Minister. This triggered front-page coverage of
Kazibwe's assumed fall from grace. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
