<HEADLINE> Five Ethiopian Civilians Killed by Eritrean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia announced Sunday that
five Ethiopian civilians were killed by the Eritrean forces in
recent clashes in Badme and Sheraro districts in northwestern
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted Daniel Kidane, local
militia head of the western Tigray zone, as saying that Eritrean
troops have destroyed a health post, an elementary school and a
building hosting the office of Badme district administration.
</P>
<P>
Among the dead are an expecting mother and two mid-wives at
the Badme Clinic, Daniel said, adding the Eritean troops took
hostages eight others civilians.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that the Ethiopian side disclosed
details of losses from the clashes with Eritrean forces.
</P>
<P>
Following the skirmishes, 16 Ethiopian schools were closed, forcing
5,000 students to quit classes and more than 300 people have now
taken refuge in Sheraro district still without shelter, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
"The displaced, including public servants, fled Badme in the
aftermath of the occupation by the Eritrean forces," said the
report, adding that "the victims were ill-treated by the invading
army which also took hostage unspecified number of people."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, three Ethiopian regions Sunday condemned the
aggression by Eritrea in their separately statements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
