<HEADLINE> 4 Children Killed in Grenade Explosion in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Four children were killed and two
others wounded in a grenade explosion in southeastern Turkey on
Sunday, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the children found the grenade when they
were playing at an open area in Kulp town of Diyarbakir province.
</P>
<P>
The grenade exploded when the children were on their way home.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the wounded were rushed to Diyarbakir
State Hospital for treatment and the investigations into the
explosive incident are underway. 
</P>
