<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for Expansion of Ties With Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Majlis Speaker Ali Akbar
Nateq Nouri Sunday called for expansion of the relations between
Tehran and Kuala Lumpur in political, economic and cultural fields.
</P>
<P>
According to Tehran radio, Nouri told visiting Speaker of the
Malaysian House of Representatives Mohammad Zahir Ismail at a
meeting here that exchange of visits between the two countries
will cement the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He expected that the parliaments of the two countries will
also develop cooperation through establishing friendly groups.
</P>
<P>
Ismail, who arrived here Sunday afternoon for a week-long
visit, replied that Malaysia is ready to expand relations with
Iran and between the two parliaments. 
</P>
