<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blair Highly Praises China's Role in Dealing With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BIRMINGHAM, May 17 (Xinhua) - Tony Blair, British Prime
Minister and the President of the G8 Summit, highly praised
China's positive role in dealing with the Asian economic crisis
here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
How to respond to the recent Asian economic crisis is one of
the main topics on the Summit's agenda.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the end of the Summit, Blair told reporters:
"We paid particular tribute in the discussion we had this morning
to the work that China has done in the aftermath of the Asian
economic crisis and to its very strong commitment to financial
stability."
</P>
<P>
Blair said that the more stable the economic and financial
system in China is, the better it is for Asia and the economies of
Asia.
</P>
<P>
"What I wanted to say and draw attention to in my remarks to
you was in a sense to congratulate China on the very firm position
it has taken particularly in respect of ruling out devaluation,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
However, commenting on how China has contributed to the process
of bringing back stability to Asia, Blair said, "I think there is
a recognition that there is still a long way to go in that region
generally."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, French President Jacques Chirac also paid to the
Chinese government for its highly-respected response to the Asian
financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
He stressed if the Chinese currency were devaluated after all,
the Asian financial crisis would have produced "catastrophic
consequences" to the world economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
