<DOCNO> XIE19980518.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Appeals to AL to Protect Aqsa Mosque </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) President Yasser Arafat called on Arab League (AL) on Sunday
to exert efforts to protect the Al Aqsa Mosque in East Jerusalem,
Islam's third holiest shrine, from Israeli aggression.
</P>
<P>
In a message to AL Secretary General Ahmed Esmat Abdel-Meguid,
Arafat warned against the "Israeli heinous crime to destroy the
mosque," Palestinian permanent delegate to the league Mohamad
Sobeih, who delivered the message, said.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian leader said that more efforts should be
mobilized through Arab foreign ministers and active organizations
all over the world to save the mosque.
</P>
<P>
The PNA has condemned Israeli extremists for damaging one of
the seven gates leading to the Al Aqsa Mosque compound on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Sobeih said the AL chief will send messages to the Arab foreign
ministers and a number of organizations, urging them to try to
prevent this mean crime. 
</P>
