<HEADLINE> OIC Criticizes India's Nuclear Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The Saudi-based Organization
of Islamic Conference (OIC) said Sunday that it is worried about
the recent Indian nuclear tests.
</P>
<P>
The OIC Secretary General Ezzidine Laraki said in a statement,
a copy of which was obtained here, that the tests "constitute a
threat to the security of southeast Asia and undermine the efforts
to establish a nuclear free zone in the region."
</P>
<P>
