the dangerous threat to its national security" posed by India's
nuclear tests.
</P>
<P>
India conducted a total of five underground nuclear tests on
May 11 and 13, claiming Pakistan and China are its security
threats.
</P>
<P>
The tests drew harsh criticism from across the world, with some
countries like the United States, Japan and Canada announcing
sanctions. 
