<HEADLINE> India's Industrial Growth Slips to 4.2 Percent in 1997-98 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 18 (Xinhua) -- India's industrial growth rate
slipped to 4.2 percent during 1997-98 (April 1, 1997-March 31,
1998) from 7.1 percent in the previous year, according to official
data available here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The robust 6.8 percent growth in the electricity sector and a
4.9 percent growth in mining during the period were offset by a
very low growth of 3.6 percent in the manufacturing sector,
considered the engine of industrial growth. The manufacturing
sector had a growth rate of 8.6 percent during 1996-97, the data
said.
</P>
<P>
The poor performance of the manufacturing sector was largely
due to a negative growth in the capital goods sub-sector. As
against a 5.9 percent growth in 1996-97, this key segment of the
manufacturing industry posted a negative growth of four percent
during 1997-98, the data said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
