<HEADLINE> Raidi Elected Chairman of Tibet Regional People's Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Raidi was elected chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Seventh Tibet Autonomous Regional
People's Congress at its first session, held here today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile Legqog was elected chairman of the regional
people's government at the same session.
</P>
<P>
The 60-year-old Raidi, of the Tibetan nationality, was born in
Biru County, Tibet. He served as chairman of the Standing
Committee of the Tibet Autonomous Regional People's Congress and
deputy secretary of the Tibet Autonomous Regional Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) in 1993 and 1994.
</P>
<P>
He joined the CPC in 1961. After studying at the Central
Political Science and Law Cadre School from 1959 to 1962, he served as
secretary of the CPC's Nagqu Prefectural Committee, 1972-1975;
deputy secretary of the CPC's Tibet Autonomous Regional Committee
after 1975; vice-chairman of the Tibet Autonomous Regional
Revolutionary Committee, 1977-1979; vice-chairman of the Standing
Committee of the Tibet Regional People's Congress, 1979-1983; and
chairman of the Fourth and Fifth CPPCC Tibet Autonomous Regional
Committees, 1986-1993.
</P>
<P>
Elected chairman of the Standing Committee of the Sixth Tibet
Autonomous Regional People's Congress, 1993. Elected deputy
secretary of the Fifth CPC Tibet Autonomous Regional Committee in
1995. Alternate member of the 11th CPC Central Committee; member
of the 12th to 15th CPC Central Committees. Deputy to Eighth NPC.
</P>
<P>
Legqog, 54, is of the Tibetan nationality and was born in
Gyangze, Tibet.
</P>
<P>
He has served as the deputy secretary of the CPC Committee of
the Tibet Autonomous Region and vice-chairman of the regional
people's government.
</P>
<P>
Received higher education and joined the CPC in 1972; served as
primary and middle school teacher in Gyangze County 1964-1971;
political cadre in Gyangze County, 1971-1973; secretary of the
Communist Youth League of China (CYLC) Gyangze County Committee
1973-1975; secretary of the Supervisory Division of the
Organization Department of the CPC's Tibet Committee 1975; deputy
chief of the Organization Division of the Organization Department
of the CPC's Tibet Committee 1980.
</P>
<P>
Deputy head of the Organization Department of the CPC's Tibet
Committee 1980-1986; executive deputy head of the Organization
Department of the CPC's Tibet Autonomous Regional Committee
1986-1991; Standing Committee member of the CPC's Tibet Autonomous
Regional Committee and secretary of the CPC's Lhasa City Committee
1991-1994.
</P>
<P>
Appointed, 1994, and elected, 1995, deputy secretary of the
CPC's Tibet Autonomous Regional Committee, and vice-chairman of
the regional people's government in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Delegate to 14th CPC National Congress 1992.
</P>
<P>
Alternate member of 15th CPC Central Committee 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
