<DOCNO> XIE19980518.0031 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai University Presidents Leave for Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 18 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of 15 presidents in
Shanghai higher education institutes left this east China
metropolis for Taiwan today, for a ten-day educational exchange
program.
</P>
<P>
Headed by Zheng Lingde, former director of the Educational
Committee of Shanghai, the educators are the city's first visiting
group to Taiwan from higher education circles. They are from
11 famous colleges and universities in the city, including Fudan
University, Shanghai University, the Science and Engineering
University of East China, Shanghai Teachers' University and Shanghai
Television University.
</P>
<P>
The university presidents will attend a symposium on the
development and prospects for higher education with a dozen
university presidents in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the delegation will visit a number of
colleges and universities in the island province.
</P>
<P>
The education exchanges between Shanghai and Taiwan have
experienced a prosperous era in recent years, with more than
400 exchange programs conducted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, at the invitation of an educational association in
Taiwan, a delegation of 11 Shanghai middle school principals also
left today for Taiwan to attend a symposium on modernizing
teaching methods and course opening. 
</P>
