the singles matches. Denmark's world number four and Olympic
champion Poul Holst-Larsen, 32, was out of form when conceding
15-5, 16-17, 8-15 to 18th-ranked Swede Thomas Johansson, three
years his junior.
</P>
<P>
Danish head coach Henrik Lyngby later said he had predicted the
match to be a "difficult one".
</P>
<P>
China of the same group defeated Hong Kong, China 5-0 to join
Denmark in an unscalable two-win lead and the top two spots of the
group.
</P>
<P>
Denmark will play China on Wednesday to decide the group
winners.
</P>
<P>
Four-time champions Malaysia whitewashed lowly-rated
Netherlands 5-0 on Monday to join in Indonesia in an unbeatable
position to take the top two spots of Group B.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia and Malaysia are to meet each other on Wednesday, the
final day of Thomas Cup Finals group competitions, to decide who
will be the group winners.
</P>
<P>
The group competitions for Uber Cup Finals will enter the final
day on Tuesday. Indonesia take on South Korea and the Netherlands
face England in Group B while China meet Denmark and Japan play
Hong Kong, China in Group A. 
