<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, May 18 (Xinhua) -- An electronic information system
company is now operational in this special economic zone in south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Its task is to monitor and thereby speed up the container
business in this port city, which has an annual handling capacity
of one million standard containers.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen port was facing difficulty in its further development
owing to its backward electronic delivery information system.
</P>
<P>
The company will invest 15 million yuan to set up an
international standard electronic delivery information system for
the port.
</P>
<P>
Electronic information systems are expected to make a big
contribution to decreasing the country's five to six billion US
dollars annual cost of paperwork needed to monitor foreign trade
at the moment.
