<HEADLINE> Hu Xiaowen Wins Women's 200m Individual Medley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAODING, North China, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Pre-meet favorite Hu
Xiaowen captured the title of women's 200 meters individual medley
at the Chinese national swimming championships here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old Hu from Liaoning Province overcame a slow start
to storm home in two minutes 16.20 seconds. Hu set the world short
course 100m individual medley record in the World Cup meet at
Beijing last Feburary,
</P>
<P>
Xu Qian from Zhejiang finished second in 2:16.68 while the
14-year-old Ning Bo, winner of the 400m medley on the opening day,
came third in 2:17.39.
</P>
<P>
"I should have had better results if I got fully prepared in
the warm-up training. I've waited the final too long," Hu said.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that a neck injury had slowed down her performance. "I
hurt my neck in training this morning. That's a blow on my
freestyle."
</P>
<P>
Coach Han Bingyan was not satisfied with Hu's time. "That is a
poor performance," Han said. "She must have been too nervous."
</P>
<P>
Han, also coach to the world 200m individual medley record
holder Chen Yan, added that Hu can beat Chen in each of the four
events separately but Chen will keep her dominance as a whole in
the medley.
</P>
<P>
"Her advantage of explosive power is dommed to lose once four
events are combined," Han said of her protegee.
</P>
<P>
Chen Hua romped to win the women's 800m freestyle in 8:43.31
with Li Yan finishing second far behind in 8:46.14.
</P>
<P>
In the men's events, Du Jie won the 100m freestyle in 52.11
while Zhu Yi captured the 200m breaststroke in 2:18.35. 
</P>
</TEXT>
