<DOCNO> XIE19980518.0055 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Offers Expresslink Service to Central HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 18 (Xinhua) -- An expresslink service will be
launched on Tuesday to help passengers using the Macao
International Airport get quick and easy access to/from central
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the Macao International Airport Company
(CAM) on Monday said that the new service, which combines speed
ferry, bus transfer, baggage handling and check-in service, will
be launched jointly by CAM and the Far East Jetfoils, the major
operator of high speed ferry services between Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
Passengers using the new service will get quicker and easier
service from central Hong Kong to the Macao airport, or vice
versa. Customs procedure will be simplified with the service.
</P>
<P>
The new measure is believed to aim at improving the
competitiveness of the Macao airport as the Hong Kong new airport
is to be inaugurated very soon, analysts said.
</P>
<P>
The Macao airport has opened air routes to more than a dozen
destinations, mainly in China's inland areas, Taiwan, some
Southeast Asian nations and parts of Europe. Its main favorable
factor in the upcoming competition is believed to be its cheaper
price, according to some analysts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
