<HEADLINE> Technology Leaders Meet to Look Ahead at Asia's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 18 (Xinhua) -- A conference focusing on the
development and future of information technology (IT) in the Asia
Pacific region opened here Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa officiated the opening of the
conference, entitled the "Future of Information and Communications
Technology in Asia."
</P>
<P>
Approximately 100 technology innovators and business leaders
from Asia, North America and Europe attended the four-day
conference to look into the impact of new technology as well as
related key issues and challenges in the Asia Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Mary O'Hara-Devereaux, director of the Institute for the
Future and leader of the conference, told reporters that the
participants will take a look at what's going on in the
information technology area in the Asia Pacific region, including
government policies, technology being used in education and
households, and other aspects.
</P>
<P>
Also, the conference will study the globalization of
information technology, or the evolving "Global Silicon Network"
formed by the emerging IT industries in countries other than the
United States, home country of the Silicon Valley.
</P>
<P>
The conference is organized by the California-based Institute
for the Future, the Asia Foundation and the Transtech Services
Limited of Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
