<HEADLINE> HKSAR Welcomes Visa-free Arrangement with Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 18 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) of China on Monday expressed
its welcome to the decision by the Government of the Republic of
Chile to grant visa-free access for a period of up to three months
for holders of HKSAR passports.
</P>
<P>
Director of Immigration Regina Ip said on Monday that the
decision reflects the strong confidence of the Government of the
Republic of Chile in Hong Kong's continued success and reaffirms
the world-class status of the HKSAR passport.
</P>
<P>
"The HKSAR Government continues to welcome citizens of the
Republic of Chile to visit Hong Kong," she said.
</P>
<P>
Currently, citizens of the Republic of Chile may visit Hong
Kong visa-free for up to three months.
</P>
<P>
The visa-free access arrangement has come into effect following
the exchange of Agreement on Mutual Exemption of Visa Requirements
between the Consul General of the Republic of Chile in Hong Kong,
Hernan Brantes, and Ip. 
</P>
