<HEADLINE> China to Educate and Rectify Procuratorial Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Strengthening education and
rectification work of the procuratorial force is a precondition
for the procuratorial organs to do a better job, chief procurators
from all parts of the country announced at a meeting here today.
</P>
<P>
The four-day meeting, which closed today, was held to encourage
procuratorial organs at all levels to strengthen education and
rectification work of the procuratorial personnel across the
country.
</P>
<P>
"If we don't make the utmost efforts to strengthen the work, it
will not only hamper the healthy development of our work but also
make it difficult for us to consolidate the progress we have
already achieved," said Liang Guoqing, deputy chief procurator of
the Supreme People's Procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
More attention should be paid to the quality of work, he
emphasized, adding that no quotas should be imposed on the number
of cases handled, and handling cases just to make profits is
strictly prohibited.
</P>
<P>
The supervision system should be strengthened to make the
procuratorial force strictly abide by the law, and there is no
pretext upon which it may break regulations or laws, he said.
</P>
<P>
The decision of the meeting should be carried out among
procuratorial organs at all levels, especially grassroots levels,
asked Liang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
