<HEADLINE> British Foreign Secretary to Visit Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Turkey announced on Monday that
British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook is scheduled to arrive here
on Tuesday for discussions on Turkish-European ties.
</P>
<P>
Cook's upcoming one-day trip is believed to be part of European
Union's (EU) efforts to mend the fences with Turkey. Britain is
currently holding the rotating presidency of the EU.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Cook will hold talks with Turkish Prime
Minister Mesut Yilmaz and his Turkish counterpart Ismail Cem,
Turkish Foreign Ministry spokesman Necati Utkan told a weekly news
briefing.
</P>
<P>
The talks will focus on ways of promoting the Turkey-European
Union relations, Utkan said, adding that the British foreign
secretary will also set forth EU's strategy for Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The ties between Turkey and the EU have been tense since Ankara
was excluded from EU's enlargement process last December for
various reasons, particularly the strained ties with
Greece. Ankara has halted political dialog with the EU.
</P>
<P>
Analysts have noted that Cook, whose visit to Ankara has been
postponed for several times, is expected to persuade Turkey to
attend the routine Turkish-EU Council meeting due on May 25.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980518.0067 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKSAR Government Continues Efforts to Tackle Unemployment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Joseph Wong, secretary for
education and manpower of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, reaffirmed here Monday the government's determination to
do all within its power to help the unemployed to re-enter the
labor market.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing on Monday, Wong said that he was
acutely aware of the difficulties faced by the unemployed.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest labor force statistics released Monday
by the Census and Statistics Department, the seasonally adjusted
unemployment rate for the period January-March 1998 was 3.5
percent, and the underemployment rate was 1.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
For the period February-April 1998, the provisional seasonally
adjusted unemployment rate was 3.9 percent, while the provisional
underemployment rate was 2.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
"Our prime tasks remain to help the unemployed find jobs, and
to provide them with training and retraining in the requisite
skills to stay competitive in the work force, so that they can
secure and hold down a job," Wong said. "We have been making
substantial progress on a series of measures," he added.
</P>
<P>
Despite the rise in unemployment rate, the Labor Department
managed to find jobs for an increasing number of job-seekers over
the past few months, Wong said.
</P>
<P>
The number of placements in April was 2,540, up 34 percent than
 that in March, and there are some 15,000 live vacancies on the
register of the Labor Department, Wong said.
</P>
<P>
On May 13, the Education and Manpower Bureau organized a
seminar to publicize to some 400 employers the latest services
provided by the Labor Department, the special tailor-made
retraining program of the Employees Retraining Board (ERB) and the
 various training programs of the Vocational Training Council.
</P>
<P>
"The seminar was well received," Wong said. "We will continue
to reach out to employers and with these pro-active efforts and
the fully computerized Local Employment Service of the Labor
Department, we should be able to place more unemployed in jobs,"
Wong said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ERB plans to spend 301 million HK dollars (38.59
 million U.S. dollars) in 1998/99 to provide 73,000 retraining
places, an increase of 37 percent in total training expenditure
and an increase of 12,000 training places over 1997/98.
</P>
<P>
Wong said that the Construction Industry Training Authority
(CITA) would launch shortly a Co-operative Training Scheme between
 CITA and contractors of the construction industry in special
trades.
</P>
<P>
"This is a new mode of training with good development
potential," Wong said. "This will foster a closer partnership
between CITA and the industry in providing training programs for
the construction industry," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Vocational Training Council (VTC) will launch a Business
Starter Program next month. Wong said that the program had met
with enthusiastic response.
</P>
<P>
To tie in with this program, VTC is planning to set up a
business Start-up Center to provide practical assistance and
support to business starters, Wong added.
</P>
<P>
Wong said that the employment prospects in the labor market
remained positive. The heavy investment in infrastructure
development program will give rise to many job opportunities over
the next few years, Wong said.
</P>
<P>
Wong said that the Task Force on Employment chaired by the
Financial Secretary Donald Tsang would have its first meeting on
June 3, and preparatory work was in full swing.
</P>
<P>
The Task Force will address the unemployment and job creation
issues in a pragmatic and constructive manner, and will seek to
devise additional practical measures to help the unemployed, Wong
emphasized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980518.0068 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Securities Market Scores Notable Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 18 (Xinhua) -- The fledgling securities market in
China has scored rapid expansion, with 775 companies listed on the
domestic stock market and another 43 overseas at the end of April.
</P>
<P>
The expanding market had claimed a capitalization of more than
two trillion yuan by the end of April, up 18.7 percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the nation's securities investors had exceeded 33
million by the end of April.
</P>
<P>
The number of securities intermediaries had risen to 327 at the
end of April, and more than 2,440 securities operations branches
have been set up across the nation.
</P>
<P>
Stock analysts say the emerging securities market and
increasing number of securities investors has enabled the
securities market to play an increasingly important role in
China's overall economy.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in the first four months this year stock
placement helped Chinese enterprises raise 30 percent more funds
than the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
China's securities market has entered a development period of
standardization and become an indispensable part of the country's
market economy system, Zhou Zhengqing, chairman of the China
Securities Regulatory Commission, said here today.
</P>
<P>
The stock market has helped raise more than 250 billion yuan
through stock placement, which has not only pulled cash-strapped
state enterprises out of financial difficulties but also
facilitated the transformation of their management mode in the
direction of becoming more market-sensitive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
