<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Meets Syrian Visitors (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here today that China has been closely following the development
of the Middle East situation and wishes to advance the Middle East
peace process together with the international community.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also General Secretary of the Chinese Communist
Party (CPC) Central Committee, made the statement at a meeting with
a visiting delegation of Syria's Arab Baath Socialist Party led by
its Deputy General Secretary Abdulla al Ahmar.
</P>
<P>
China has always supported the Arabian people in their just cause,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The realization of an all-round, just and lasting peace in the
Middle East not only conforms to the interests of Syria and other
Middle East countries, but also benefits the peace and stability
of the world as a whole, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Syria has, in recent years, placed particular
importance on its external relations, positively promoted the
Middle East peace process, and is playing an increasingly
important role in the region, a fact that has received universal
attention.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China and Syria have a traditional friendship, and
the frequent exchanges of visits between leaders of the two
countries in recent years and their exchanges of views on issues
of common concern have furthered mutual understanding and bolstered
the constant development of the friendly cooperative relations in
various sectors of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"We are satisfied with this," Jiang added.
</P>
</TEXT>
