<HEADLINE> More Departure Flights For Dutch Citizens in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 18 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Netherlands
decided on Monday to charter additional aircraft to operate
shuttle flights to Singapore for Dutch citizens living and working
in Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
A military KDC10 was also put on standby in Singapore to
provide backup, a foreign ministry official said.
</P>
<P>
"This is not an evacuation, but offering the maximum
opportunity to leave," said Foreign Ministry Secretary-General
Dirk Jan van den Berg.
</P>
<P>
Such "departure" flights have been transporting Dutch citizens
from Indonesia, a former colony of the Netherlands, for the
past few days, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
A crisis center was set up to monitor the latest developments
in the Indonesian situation, and the center is advised through
video-linked consultations with Jakarta twice a day.
</P>
<P>
Other countries have also begun to provide evacuation flights
during the past few days as riots in Indonesia increase.  
</P>
