<HEADLINE> Chinese, Surinamese Presidents Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 18 (Xinhua) -- China treasures the traditional
friendship with Surinam and is ready to collaborate with it to
forge a long-term and stable friendly relationship of cooperation
oriented toward the 21st century, President Jiang Zemin said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and his Surinamese counterpart Jules Wijdenbosch held
talks in a cordial and friendly atmosphere this afternoon, in
which they had an in-depth exchange of views on bilateral
relations and other issues of common concern, and reached a
wide-ranging consensus.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said Wijdenbosch's ongoing China tour will surely serve
to further promote bilateral relations, and make bilateral
friendship and mutually beneficial cooperation score more
successes.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the two countries cherish a deep traditional
friendship and, since they established diplomatic ties 22 years
ago, bilateral cooperation in the political, economic, military
and cultural sectors have been fruitful.
</P>
<P>
On international issues, Jiang went on to say, the two nations
have supported and closely cooperated with each other. "We are
satisfied with the great development in China-Surinam relations,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the Surinamese government and Wijdenbosch
for their positive contributions to enhancing bilateral relations
and for their understanding and support for Chinese people's
endeavour for peaceful reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the Chinese government regards Surinam as an
important cooperation partner in the Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
Wijdenbosch said that he was glad to visit China, and praised
the Chinese residing in his country for their hard work and
contributions to furthering the friendship between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said his government values Surinam-China relations and
bilateral friendly cooperative ties extend to all areas.
</P>
<P>
The president reiterated that his government will continue to
stick to the "one China" policy, and join the Chinese government
in promoting bilateral friendly cooperation in the political,
economic and cultural fields to score new progress.
</P>
