<HEADLINE> Turkey Concerned About Kurds' Meeting in Cairo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Turkey on Monday expressed its
concern about the upcoming meeting of several Kurdish groups in
northern Iraq, which will be held in Cairo, capital of Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a weekly press conference here, Turkish Foreign
Ministry spokesman Necati Utkan said that the Turkish Embassy in
Egypt will be closely following the meeting scheduled for
May 27-28.
</P>
<P>
