invited to the meeting in a formal or informal way," Utkan said.
</P>
<P>
The PKK, which has been declared by Ankara as an illegal
organization, has been fighting a 14-year-old war against the
Turkish government for the establishment of an independent Kurdish
state in southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The Cairo meeting is organized by a non-governmental
institution called Asian-African Solidarity Organization,
according to media reports.
</P>
<P>
Responding to a question by Cumhuriyet, a leading Turkish
newspaper, Egyptian Ambassador to Turkey Muhammed Mehdi Fathala
said that the meeting has no connections with the Egyptian
government. 
