<HEADLINE> Gruev Dropped From Bulgaria World Squad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Midfielder Ilia Gruev was cut off
from the Bulgarian World Cup squad by coach Hristo Bonev, who
abandoned earlier promises to help the player clear his name of
doping charges.
</P>
<P>
Bonev said he had talked the case with the head of the
Bulgarian doping control laboratory and then decided that Gruev
would be out of his World Cup plan.
</P>
<P>
Gruev has already been suspended by the Bulgarian soccer
federation, faces a two-year ban after last month testing
positive for the banned anabolic nortestosterone.
</P>
<P>
Bonev reacted strongly in Gruyev's defence 10 days ago then. "I
will struggle tooth-and-nail for this lad as I know him very well
and I am sure that he cannot not do such a thing," Bonev said.
</P>
<P>
"He is innocent and I will prove it. Ilia Gruev will play in
the World Cup finals," he said, adding he would send a fresh
Gruyev's sample to an internationally-recognized laboratory in
Cologne.
</P>
<P>
The coach then named the 28-year-old from Neftochimik Bourgas
in squad for a training camp beginning on Monday and Bonev said
the final squad of 22 players would be named only one day ahead of
the June 2 deadline set by FIFA. 
</P>
