<HEADLINE> 3 Lebanese Civilians Wounded by Israeli Shelling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Three Lebanese civilians were
wounded by Israeli artillery shelling in south Lebanon Monday,
Lebanon's Orient radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The three were wounded at dawn of the day when Israeli shells
landed at the village of Majdal Silm in the western sector of the
Israeli occupied border zone in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israeli warplanes also swooped down on several villages in the
Iqlim Toufah area on the edge of the central part of the zone,
according to the radio.
</P>
<P>
These places are believed to be the bases used by Lebanese
guerrillas to launch offensives against Israeli posts inside the
zone.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, said in a
statement that one of its units had set off a roadside bomb when a
group of Israeli soldiers were patrolling on a road inside the
zone.
</P>
<P>
The attack killed or wounded some of the Israeli soldiers, the
statement added.
</P>
<P>
The latest clashes between Israeli troops and Hezbollah began
late last night in the western sector of the zone, in which
Israeli troops fired surface-to-surface missiles toward their
targets, according to Lebanese security sources.
</P>
<P>
Another Lebanese anti-Israeli occupation military group Amal
Movement, led by Parliament Speaker Nabih Berri, also announced
that it launched separate attacks on Israeli posts inside the zone
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Israel is occupying a 1,200-square-kilometer border strip in
south Lebanon with the aim of protecting its northern areas from
Lebanese guerrilla cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
There have been frequent clashes since the establishment of
the zone in 1985 between Israeli troops and guerrillas who are
trying to oust them from the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
