<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SightFirst China Action Donates 100 Artificial Lenses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, May 18 (Xinhua) -- A cataract sufferer from a
poverty-stricken area in northwest China's Gansu Province received
a free operation here today to replace his diseased crystalline
lens.
</P>
<P>
The Gansu Center for SightFirst China Action, initiated by the
worldwide non-governmental charity organization, the Lion Clubs,
donated 100 artificial crystalline lenses for local patients who are
in financial straits.
</P>
<P>
The Lanzhou Air Force Hospital, where the operation was
performed, has dispatched medical groups to help rural poor people
throughout the province.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, the province has started a
one-month poverty relief program for its 192,000 disabled living
in poverty.
</P>
<P>
SightFirst China Action aims at helping cataract sufferers
all over China. It is active in most Chinese provinces.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
