<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Hits 12,500 Against U.S. dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 18 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian rupiah closed at
12,500 against the U.S. dollar at the Jakarta spot market Monday.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah traded at 10,800 per dollar on May 14. However,
trading was sluggish since last week's widespread rioting in
Jakarta sent jitters to market players, a trader said here.
</P>
<P>
"Investors are still taking a wait-and-see attitude, There was
still a slight volume of activity in the market," he added.
</P>
<P>
Rupiah liquidity was relatively tight with overnight inter-bank
call money ranging from 52 percent to 53 percent, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The value of rupiah has lost more than 70 percent against the
greenback since July last year. 
</P>
