<HEADLINE> Leading Marine Chemical Plant Issues Stocks in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, May 18 (Xinhua) -- The initial public offering (IPO) of
shares of China's leading marine chemical plant was made available
today on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The Shandong Marine Chemical Co. Ltd. offered to the public 108
million shares at 5.23 yuan (0.63 dollars) per share.
</P>
<P>
The company's total share capital stands at 420 million shares,
including 300 million "legal-person" shares and 120 million public
shares (of which 18 million shares are offered to its
employees). The controlling shareholder is the Shandong Marine
Chemical Group, which holds 71.43 percent of the shares.
</P>
<P>
A company source told Xinhua that the 600 million yuan (72.29
million US dollars) of funds raised will be used for the
development of 15 varieties of products and technical
transformation designed to generate more than 980 million yuan
(118 million US dollars) of sales and 235 million yuan (28.3
million US dollars) of profits annually.
</P>
<P>
Coastal Shandong Province in east China has an ideal
environment for developing the marine chemical industry and is the
largest marine chemical manufacturer and exporter in the country.
 
</P>
