Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Monday in quiet trading on
continued selling pressure on selective heavyweights after last
week's two-day rebound.
</P>
<P>
Volume was thin as dealers said investors were mostly sidelined
awaiting clearer directions over the political unrest in
Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index fell 16.86
points to 549.99, the all-share Emas Index eased 4.02 points to
138.92 and the Industrial Index dropped 29.54 points to 1,065.78
while the Second Board Index also shed 2.43 points to 121.35.
</P>
<P>
Losers thumped gainers by 540 to 81, while 114 counters were
unchanged and 181 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's volume shrunk to 99.090 million shares worth 215.220
million ringgit (about 56.0468 million U.S. dollars) from 129.504
million shares valued at 305.388 million ringgit (about 79.5281
million U.S. dollars) on Friday.
