190.929 million ringgit (about 49.721 million U.S. dollars) from
103.685 million shares valued at 262.362 million ringgit (about
68.3234 million U.S. dollars) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover dropped to 16.485 million shares
worth 24.290 million ringgit (about 6.3255 million U.S. dollars)
from Friday's 25.819 million shares valued at 43.026 million
ringgit (about 11.204 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover rose to 5.947 million shares worth 33.175
million ringgit (about 8.639 million U.S. dollars) from 905,000
million shares valued at 5.225 million ringgit (about 1.36 million
U.S. dollars) on Friday. 
