<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Prince of Luxembourg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 18 (Xinhua)-- China will make continuous efforts to
develop and strengthen its friendly cooperation with Luxembourg
and all other countries of the European Union (EU), Li Peng, the
top Chinese legislator, said here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC), made this remark while meeting Prince Henri and
Minister of Economic Affairs Robert Goebbels of Luxembourg.
</P>
<P>
Li praised the development of the bilateral relations and the
friendly cooperation between China and Luxembourg. The two
countries have scored remarkable achievements in cooperation in
the sectors of finance, metallurgy and health. Luxembourg has
accumulated much experience in these fields, which China can learn
from, Li told the guests.
</P>
<P>
Li also briefed the prince and his party on the functions of
the NPC and the work it has done in law formulation, supervision
and China's legal and democratic construction.
</P>
<P>
The prince told Li that the ministers, bankers and
entrepreneurs who came to China with him this time are very
interested in China's development, and they have already made
fruitful contacts with their Chinese counterparts during their
short stay in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
He said that Luxembourg also values its relationship with China
and is willing to help strengthen the links between the EU and
China.  
</P>
