<HEADLINE> Industrial Accidents Drop in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 18 (Xinhua) -- The number of victims who suffered
from industrial accidents last year dropped by 5 percent in Macao
from a year before, the latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Labor and Employment Department
on Monday show that accidents in work killed a total of eight
people, a drop of 42.9 percent from 1996, and permanently disabled
the working ability of 22 others.
</P>
<P>
In addition, among the 3,558 victims recorded in 1997, 2,848
lost their working ability temporarily due to injuries.
</P>
<P>
Most accidents happened in such businesses as shops,
restaurants, hotels and construction sites. Some 62 percent of the
victims were aged between 25 and 44. 
</P>
</TEXT>
