<HEADLINE> HK, Maldives Sign Air Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong and Maldives, an island
country in South Asia, signed an air services transit
agreement Monday in Male, the capital of Maldives, according to
Hong Kong's Government Information Services Department.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Secretary for Economic Services Stephen Ip and
Mahmood Razee, the director of civil aviation of Maldives, signed
the agreement.
</P>
<P>
This is the first overflight agreement that the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region government has ever signed with any
country, Ip told the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The agreement provides a legal framework for airlines to use
the most direct and cost-effective flight paths for their
international services, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong official said: "Acting under the authorization of
the Central People's Government, we will continue to conclude more
overflight agreements with other countries."
</P>
<P>
Currently, Cathay Pacific Airways' service to South Africa
needs to fly over Maldives en route to Johannesburg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
