<HEADLINE> Anhui Expressway Ltd Reports Good Business on HK Bourse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, May 18 (Xinhua) -- The Anhui Expressway Co. Ltd, China's
first highway enterprise listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange,
reported a good business performance last year, according to an
annual meeting of shareholders today.
</P>
<P>
The listed company's business income and post-tax profits both
hit record highs of 225.7 million yuan and 139.6 million yuan last
year, up 37.3 and 54.3 percent respectively, according to the
company's accounting report compiled in line with standard
international practice.
</P>
<P>
The record figures translate into a per-share earning level of
0.0991 yuan and a per-share dividend of 0.02 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Anhui Expressway operates part of the Nanjing-Shanghai
Expressway, which had a daily flow of 11,000 vehicles last year,
and part of the National Highway 205, which runs from Shanhaiguan in
north China's Hebei Province, to Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Anhui Expressway was listed on the HK Stock Exchange on
November 13, 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
