<HEADLINE> China's Largest Retail Book Store Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 18 (Xinhua) -- China's largest book retailer today
opened to the public in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Book Center -- jointly funded by the Xinhua Bookstore
Beijing Branch, China Bookstore and the Foreign Languages
Bookstore -- is on Chang'an Street near the busy commercial
district of Xidan.
</P>
<P>
The 11-story building, with a total building space of more than
50,000 square meters, can display more than 100,000 titles. It has
established business links with about 500 publishing houses
throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
Managers of the book center will oversee the entire business
through a computerized management network. The center also
includes restaurants and entertainment, managers said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
