<HEADLINE> Cuba Offers Help to Boost Aquaculture in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Cuba has offered to help boost
Malaysia's aquaculture industry by sending several experts here,
Malaysian Agriculture Minister Amar Sulaiman Daud said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Cuba has also invited Malaysia to send its officials there to
learn more about aquaculture, he told reporters here after meeting
visiting Cuban Fisheries Minister Orlando Felipe Rodgroquez Romay.
</P>
<P>
"Their stress is on boosting the rearing of freshwater fish, "
Sulaiman said, adding Malaysia must step-up freshwater fish
breeding because of the drop in marine fish resources.
</P>
<P>
Freshwater fish could also be used as feed for the livestock
industry in place of maize and soybean which are mainly imported
at a high cost, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the Cabinet had asked Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad
Badawi, who is to visit Cuba soon, to further discuss the
cooperation in aquaculture industry between the two sides.
</P>
</TEXT>
