<HEADLINE> China's Anhui Extends Telephone Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, May 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province will have
extended its network of program-controlled telephone switchboards
to all of its villages by the end of 1999, according to a recent
provincial government decision.
</P>
<P>
To ensure the realization of the projected goal, a leading
group led by a vice governor has been formed.
</P>
<P>
Anhui, which has 30,502 villages, has reported significant
progress in building up its telecommunications system in the rural
areas since 1991.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that the telephone switchboard
capacity of rural Anhui had reached 1.03 million lines by the end
of 1997. Some 550,000 rural families had installed telephones by
then.
</P>
<P>
Also by the end of last year, 23,961 of Anhui's villages had
been covered by the province's program-controlled telephone
network. 
</P>
</TEXT>
