<HEADLINE> Iran to Export 1.5 Million Tonnes of Steel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Iran will promote the its steel
production to 6.7 million tonnes and steel export to 1.5 million
tonnes during the current Iranian year (starting from March 21),
local daily Iran News reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Commercial Director of the Ministry of Mines and Metals
Hussein Erfani said on Sunday that the country expected to earn
some 440 million U.S. dollars from mining and metals exports
during this Iranian year.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the last Iranian year, Iran exported 290
million dollars worth of steel, copper, aluminum and ferroalloys,
showing a 69 percent growth in volume and 58 percent rise in
weight compared with the previous year.
</P>
<P>
It was announced last month that Iran exported 830,000 tonnes
of steel products during the last Iranian year, 85 percent more
than that of the year before.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Mines of Metals reportedly planned to boost the
annual steel production to 12 million tonnes by the end of the
second five-year development plan (1995-2000).
</P>
<P>
Iran produced 6 million tonnes of steel in 1996-97 Iranian
year, but so far there was no report about Iran's steel
production during the last Iranian year. 
</P>
