<HEADLINE> Indonesian House Hopes for Soeharto's Resignation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Speaker of Indonesia's House of
Representatives Harmoko expressed the hope here Monday that
President Soeharto would be wise enough to step down for the sake
of national unity.
</P>
<P>
Harmoko, accompanied by four deputy speakers held a brief press
conference in response to the latest development in the country.
</P>
<P>
Harmoko appealed to the people to stay calm, exercise
self-restraint, maintain unity and cohesion and uphold peace and
order so that reforms could be done constitutionally.
</P>
<P>
The house is scheduled to hold a leadership meeting on Tuesday
to discuss the matter and it will submit the results of the
meeting to President Soeharto.
</P>
<P>
The house, in Monday's leadership meeting, studied carefully
the national situation which has changed rapidly concerning the
people's aspiration for reforms, including a special session of
the People's Consultative Assembly and the resignation of
President Soeharto, Harmoko said.
</P>
<P>
He said the meetings are in line with the house's regulations
according to which a decision should be made jointly by the house
speaker and faction leaders.
</P>
<P>
"In responding to the present situation, the leadership of the
House of Representatives has hoped that the president would be
wise enough to tender his resignation for the sake of the
country's unity," Harmoko said.
</P>
<P>
Harmoko and the others left the conference room shortly after
announcing their decision without giving reporters a chance to ask
questions. 
</P>
