Minister Tony Blair avoided to let a dispute appear among the
leaders of the eight most industrialized countries by
side-stepping the issue of nuclear tests by India. But,
U.S. President Bill Clinton wished to take financial and trade
sanctions against India, in order to persuade Pakistan, and
perhaps Iran, not to follow suit. France and Russia opposed such
measures.
</P>
