<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed higher in Tokyo
Monday on buying spurred by an advance in futures prices.
</P>
<P>
The key Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the
First Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose 141.61 points or
0.93 percent from last Friday's close to 15,384.47.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, advanced 2.24 points or 0.19 percent to
1,209.17.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the the major section thinned to an estimated 320
million shares from Friday's 400 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nissan Motor was Monday's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Stock prices went down soon after the market opened in line
with a fall in the Japanese yen to the 135 yen level against the
U.S. dollar, selling prevailed at first on the stock futures
market, pushing down the key June Nikkei futures to 15,030 at one
point in the morning, traders said.
</P>
<P>
But basket buying on behalf of public funds prevented the
Nikkei average from falling below 15,000 and helped eventually to
prop it up, they said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,331 issues listed on the First Section, losers edged
gainers 554 to 509, with 188 issues remaining unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
