<HEADLINE> Income for Most Urban Residents Increases, Survey Shows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 18 (Xinhua) -- A recent sample survey shows that,
in the first quarter of this year, the monthly income for China's
urban residents reached 1,533 yuan, up 5.2 percent on a
year-on-year base.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate was 3 percent higher than in the same period
last year, according to a recent survey of 39,000 households
conducted by the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Detailed data also show that the income for residents in the
eastern part of the country was 1,880 yuan, up 5.1 percent; for
the central China, 1,240 yuan, up 5.6 percent; and for the western
part, 1,321 yuan, up 5.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Residents in the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region and Beijing municipality enjoyed the most rapid
income growth rate with Inner Mongolia at 22.2 percent, Ningxia
Hui Autonomous Region at 13.8 percent and Beijing at 10.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the income for urban residents in Jilin province in
northeast China and southwest China's Guizhou province declined.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
