<HEADLINE> Guangdong's Bonded Zones Focus on High-tech Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 18 (Xinhua) -- The Futian Bonded Zone near the
Shenzhen River has been known for its large warehouses, but now
multinational corporations such as IBM and Chia Tai of Thailand
are locating high-tech industrial businesses there.
</P>
<P>
"Land resources in the bonded zone are limited, so we will give
priorities to developing high-tech sectors and advanced
industries," said Qiu Shuming, director of the zone's
administrative bureau.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong province where the Futian Bonded Zone is located
approved the formation of six bonded areas, four of which are
operational, and used 1.27 billion U.S. dollars of overseas
investment by the end of 1997, including 276 million last year,
which mainly went to high- and new-technology projects.
</P>
<P>
The Futian Bonded Zone is making greater efforts to restructure
its storage and distribution-based industries in a bid to have 60
percent of industrial production and 15 percent of contributions
by newly emerging sectors within three years.
</P>
<P>
The Shantou Bonded Zone opened six high-tech foreign-funded
ventures last year involving diamond cutting tools, disinfectants
and computers.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou Bonded Zone is now busy negotiating with foreign
partners on building a computer city in the area, aiming to
produce three million computers, 2.5 million central processing
units, and 300,000 laptops annually over the next few years.
</P>
</TEXT>
