<P>
 More Green Land for People Tomorrow
</P>
<P>
To change the backward outlook of Bozhou's afforestation, the
staff of the Bozhou Horticultural Management Bureau, under the
leadership of the Bureau chief Tian Chengshan, have in recent
years been actively implementing the policy set by the municiple
government to turn the city into an "outstanding city along the
Jing-jiu railway (the railway linking Beijing and Kowloon).
</P>
<P>
In years before 1994, there was not a single park in the city,
and the per capita green land only accounted for 3.2 square
meters. However, in recent years, the city has gradually increased
its input on horticultural construction, with a total of more than
10 million yuan spent on afforestation. There are more than 40
hectares of new green land in the city today, or a per capita
share of more than 7 square meters.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the Emperor Tang's Tomb is a significant
event in Bozhou's horticultural history. So far complete sets of
the park have been finished. Decorated with green trees and
blooming flowers, the park has been an agreeable public place of
entertainment for people from all walks of life and is widely
commended.
</P>
<P>
Bozhou is a city with an ancient civilization. Places of
historic interest can be seen everywhere. The municiple government
has restored and reopened the Huatuo (who is a famous ancient
doctor) Memorial Hall, the Huaxi Building, the Three Kingdoms
Exhibition Hall and the Martyrs Cemetery, etc. It newly increased
30,000 square meters green land. In making city programme, the
horticultural bureau has strictly adhered to a fixed ratio between
new areas and the old ones. For instance, in restructuring the
Xinhua Road, Renmin Road and Bozhou Road, enough spaces have been
saved for future afforestation.
</P>
<P>
Through perfecting local laws, setting up a contracted
responsibility system for afforestation, synthetic control and
volunteer afforestation, Bozhou has brought its afforestation and
forest management onto a new stage.
</P>
<P>
This far, afforestation areas in the city almost make up fourty
percent of its total land. The volunteer afforestation move of the
masses also yielded notalbe results, with 45 new gardens
appeared. Measures to reinforce its afforestation laws also
worked. A supervising unit set up to guarantee the responsibilty
for afforestation was properly held by designated ones.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to such efficient measures, the city sees no incurrence
of infringing on public green land and the survival rate of trees
stays at above 90 percent.
</P>
<P>
Bozhou, the city already in green, will have a greener
tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
location: Bozhou City
</P>
<P>
Tel: (0058) 5521948
</P>
<P>
 Re-create Splendour
</P>
<P>
-- A introduction to Bozhou's private enterprise reform
</P>
<P>
With the comprehensive benefit of its village and township
enterprises ranked second in Bozhou in three successive years,
Bozhou, a nationwide model city for east-west cooperation, has
taken the advantage of all favourable policies granted to it at a
on-the-spot meeting aimed at accelerating the development of
village and township enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The city has focused on heavy input, outside-oriented services,
businesses restructuring, intensive management and fostering new
economic growing points. With the concerted efforts of 270,000
employees, village and township enterprises have demonstrated its
vitality.
</P>
<P>
As Yu Lin, head of the Bozhou Village and Township Enterprise
Committee (BVTEC), puts it, the features of the city's township
enterprises are as follows.
</P>
<P>
Firstly, the deepening of reforms has faciliated the
redirecting of capital. Through renting, merging, agglomerating,
auctioning and purchasing enterprises, Bozhou's village and
township enterprises benefit from an improved structure of
capital and accelerated capital redirecting. According to
uncompleted statisitics, Bozhou's village and township enterprise
reform, centered on reforming ownership, has set 520 enterprised
which were closed down or on the verge of bankruptcy in motion
again.
</P>
<P>
Secondly, under the principle of mutual benefit and making use
of each other's advantages, Bozhou towhship enterprises have
strengthened their cooperation in economy and technology with eastern
regions. A successful example is the cooperation between Bozhou's
Laojing brewery and the Baile brewery in China's Sichuan province,
which led to the formation of "China's Anhui Huisha Group" , a
group comprising 13 enterprises. The mega-merge was approved by
the national agricultural ministry.
</P>
<P>
Thirdly, the city has been seeking efficiency through
implementing modern management, upgrading enterprises with science
and technology and adopting the strategy of building "famous
brand". As a result, Bozhou now has two village and township
enterprise groups at the state level, six provincial "star
enterprises" , 45 enterprises considered "honest" and
"trustworthy" for their products' good quality. The city also
created 35 high-quality products of its own.
</P>
<P>
The rapid development of the 753 private enterprises in Bozhou
has strengthened the city's basic industry and improved traditional
industries as well. Some traditional industries, such as the
processing of medicines, Chinese parasols, flour, brew and
textiles, become leading industries.
</P>
<P>
To accelerate the development of township enterprises, Bozhou
has attached great importance to collecting capital through
diversified channels and increasing input. In 1997 alone, finance
departments channeled in 3.8 million yuan for township
enterprises. The reform on enterprise ownership has changed the
enterprise financing from a unique one to diversified ones, thus
completely brought money-pinching private enterprises from their
financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Location: N020 Building, Jiaoling Road, Bozhou
</P>
<P>
Tel: (0558) 5529710
</P>
<P>
 A Work of Love
</P>
<P>
 -- On Bozhou's Civil Administration
</P>
<P>
In the spirit of "sharing burden with the central government
and easing worry for the masses", Bozhou's civil administration
bureau have concentrated on reforms, development and stability. It
won many awards for its efforts to improve the city's welfare
system, help settle down veterans and building old people's homes.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Licheng, chief of the Civil Administration Bureau, and
Yao Qishun, secretary of the Communist Party of China in Bozhou,
attributed the encouraging achievement to measures stated below:
</P>
<P>
Strengthen the basis and work on improvement. The Bozhou
municiple government have in recenty years given priority to civil
administration work, setting up offices in charge of civil affairs
in villages and towns, completing grass-root civil administration
network and building old people's homes and memoriors, etc.
</P>
<P>
Advocate socialism ethics. The Bozhou civil administration
bureau and its subsidaries have made unremmitting efforts to build
socialism ethics. It has worked out a 5-year plan designed to
coordinate its material and ethics drives. The bureau has been
honored by the municipal government as a model unit.
</P>
<P>
Take the whole situation into consideration and try to maitain
stability. The Bozhou Civil Administration Bearau has successful
managed the disaster relief work and helped the poor, guaranteeing
to the maxium extend that all relief money in the city's budget
goes to its due places. It has continuously improved its work to
support helpless elders. Among the 39 old people's homes in 29
villages and towns in Bozhou, two were elected models in Anhui
Province, three were elected "civilized ones". A social security
system covering both the city and the rural regions is now taking
shape.
</P>
<P>
Strengthen national defense and help servicemen and their
families. For its work helping servicemen and honoring those give
up their lives for the country, the Civil Administration Bureau
has been praised by the provincial government in two years.
</P>
<P>
Pay close attention to grass-root management. Under the Civil
Administration Bureau's instruction, elections have been held to
740 village and residents' committees. Schools have been set up
for training village cadres.
</P>
<P>
Develop economy. The Civil Administration Bureau has put much
efforts to establishing welfare enterprises. Now, disabled people
who are still capable of working all have access to a job.
</P>
<P>
Location: Cao Gang Kou in Bozhou City
</P>
<P>
Tel: (0558) 5522373
