<P>
 Contribute to Development of Local Economy
</P>
<P>
 -- An Interview with Bozhou Taxation Bearau Chief
</P>
<P>
In recenty years, the Taxation Bearau of Bozhou city has
collected more than 0.64 billion yuan for local finance. It has
played an important role in improving the industrial structure,
faciliating the adjusting of its industrial structure and
monitoring local finance.
</P>
<P>
The Taxation Bureau, set up in August 1994, now has eight
divisions, six branch bureaus, 28 local taxation offices and one
taxation center, with a total of 293 employees.
</P>
<P>
On the current situation of Bozhou's local taxation, the bureau
chief Ma Zong Yuan sumed up four striking features:
</P>
<P>
First, the tax income has been in a stready increase and making
a growing share in local revenue. Local tax income have increased
from 72.03 million yuan in 1994 to 0.2 billion yuan today.
</P>
<P>
Second, the bureau's control over the overall economic
development has been remarkably strengthened. Taxations conducive
to economic development have been encouraged and those unjustified
under certain laws have been curbed.
</P>
<P>
Third, the structure of tax sources becomes more reasonable,
with taxation on industrial and commercial enterprises making the
main part, taxation on personal income in a sharp rise and
taxation on the added value of land, the usage of veicles, the
house ownership and stamp duties having yet potential to tap.
</P>
<P>
Fourth, reform on tax levying and management is now in the
ascendant. Since 1996, 2.4 billion yuan has been invested to build
a multi-functional modern tax center, which will increase not only
working efficiency but also the tranparency of taxation.
</P>
<P>
Ma Zongyuan said the tax bureau will work harder to make new
contribution to Bozhou's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Location: No 112, Heping Road,
</P>
<P>
Tel: (0558) 5530838 5520826
