<P>
Meet the Challenge
</P>
<P>
 -- Bozhou Labour Bureau Chief Lu Wenzhao
</P>
<P>
After being awarded the title of "the advanced unit in human
resources mangement" by the labour department and the personnel
department of Anhui Province in 1996, Bozhou Labour Bureau in 1997
again won the first place in six special respects, namely the
employment of workers, their payment, workers' safety,
arbitration of related disputes and work supervision.
</P>
<P>
To gain the achievements, the Labour Bureau chief Lu Wenzhao
worked hard and shed too much sweet.
</P>
<P>
When Lu took office as the labour chief in October 1991, he
knew little about his new post. However, less than a year later,
he learnt by himself all needed academic knowledge and won related
diplomacy. Under his leadership, the Labour Bureau worked out a
package of laws and regulations to guide their work, and greatly
helped the building of a clean government.
</P>
<P>
Lu said: "The re-employment of the layoffs affected numerious
families, and it also bears impact on the country's economic
development and social stability" .
</P>
<P>
To tackle the problem of unemployment, Lu and his colleagues
bend on increasing channels for workers' reemployment. Using media
reports to show the public difficulties laying ahead and win their
understanding and backing, Lu and his colleagues help the layoffs
establish a proper attitude towards their reemployment.
</P>
<P>
They also try to open new ways both helpful to layoffs'
reemployment and the development of economy. The bureau has
resettled 3217 layoffs. Tian Guiying, a woman who lost her job in
an enterprise trimming, now becomes a success with her new career
and is elected a deputy to the provincial people's congress.
</P>
<P>
With government departments being streamlined and Bozhou
becoming municipality directly under the provincial government, Lu
said they are faced with even greater challenge. However, they are
fully prepared, he said.
</P>
<P>
Location: Xinhua Road, Bozhou
</P>
<P>
Tel: (0558) 5516005
