<P>
Embrace a Bumpy Harvest
</P>
<P>
 -- reforms on financial system of Bozhou
</P>
<P>
For its progess in reforming financial management, Bozhou
Finance Bureau was awarded the title of "advanced unit" by the
Anhui provincial government. It was also honored in two seccussive
years as a nationwide "advanced unit" for its accounts clearing
work.
</P>
<P>
Adhering to development and reform, Bozhou's financial
departments in recent years have accomplished great reform to its
tax and finance system, great conversion of concept of how to
manage money, and great increase to its revenue.
</P>
<P>
The revenue of the city has maintained an annual growth rate of
37.2 precent in recent years. The net annual increase of revenue
remains close to 0.1 billion yuan. Revenue has made up 10.1
percent of the city's overall income.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to a series of major steps by the municipal government
to develop economy, the city's financial resoures have been
adjusted and become more reasonable. Its ten development projects,
headed by the Gujing Brewery, have been further improved and its
service sector is developing rapidly. A number of newly-built
enterprises, such as the new tobacco company, the battery company
and the diamond company, become new financial resoures for the
city.
</P>
<P>
More financial spending go to some chosen projects, which means
a more efficient use of the revenue. The finance bureau has made
concrete measures to reduce public money spent in meetings and
telephone fees. Mangement of personnel has been tightened and
reform on the state-paid medical care system has been carried
on. With the continuous bettering of the financial spending
composition, money going to production and construction increases
year by year. Now there has been a total of 385.54 million yuan
spent on production and construction.
</P>
<P>
Management of village finance has been improved. Villages are
now given more freedom to handle their finance, and are also
responsible for the mangement of their revenue. As a result, the
revenue at village-level has been increasing by 62.2 percent
yearly, bringing its share in the city's total revenue up to 35.1
percent. There are 9 villages with a revenue of more than 10
million yuan, among which two villages' revenue exceeded 20
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Financial organs also strengthened the control over capital out
of the government budget. After several years of investigation,
some 80 million yuan out of the budget has been placed on bank
accounts opened by financial organs. With the comprehensive
management of capital out of the budget, the portion of money has
been handled in a more standard, scientific and legal way. And
the continued bettering of financial laws leads to an overall
improvement of financial work.#

