<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, May 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO -- The Japanese government decided Monday to dispatch its
military transport planes to Singapore to stand by for evacuation
of Japanese nationals in the riot-racked Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Two C-130H transport planes of the Air Self-Defense Force
(ASDF) will leave the Komaki air base in Aichi Prefecture, central
Japan, on Tuesday for Singapore via Manila, Japanese government
officials said. Currently, there are about 13,600 Japanese
nationals and an unconfirmed number of Japanese tourists in
Indonesia. (Japan-Indonesia-Evacuation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Cambodians began Monday to head for the Buddhist
temples and schools, voter registration centers for the general
election scheduled for July 26.
</P>
<P>
Registration opened about 7:00 a.m. local time and would last
28 days to June 15. Cambodia, with a population of 10.45 million,
has 5.43 million eligible voters who will elect 122 parliament
members in the election. (Cambodia-Voter Registration)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan reminded
American students that too many people are still thinking about
international issues "in local terms, constrained by boundaries."
</P>
<P>
Annan, who made the remarks Sunday at Macalester College in
St. Paul, Minnesota, said that issues in the face of the
185-member-state United Nations such as environment, drugs,
pandemics, sustainable development are all issues cutting across
all frontiers. (UN-Annan) 
</P>
