<HEADLINE> China Preparing for World Horticulture Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Preparations are under way for the
world horticulture fair, which is scheduled to be held in China's
southwestern city of Kunming in May through October of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Five exhibition halls, three outdoor exhibition areas, six
exhibition gardens with special themes and a framework of public
facilities are being built on the site of the exhibition, which is
expected to cover 218 hectares.
</P>
<P>
The fair, the biggest of its kind in the world and the only
large international event the Chinese government will host before
the turn of this century, has an organization committee directed
by Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing.
</P>
<P>
All the construction and horticultural projects for the fair
are expected to be finished by the end of this year and other
related facilities, including the expansion of Kunming
International Airport, are also well under way, said an official
of the organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
More than 70 countries and international organizations have so
far applied to participate in the fair, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The official also predicted that the fair would attract more
than 100 countries and international organizations and nearly
10,000 enterprises from home and abroad, as well as eight million
visitors.
</P>
<P>
The fair, with a theme of the relationship between humans and
nature in the 21st century, will concentrate on displaying a
variety of indoor and outdoor horticultural masterpieces from
China and foreign countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
