<HEADLINE> Domestic Products Increasing In China's Electronics Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Domestic brands have begun to play
a leading role in China's electronics information market,
offsetting the overwhelming superiority that Japanese products had
in the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Chinese TV brands like Changhong, Konca, Panda, and TCL sell
for about half the price of foreign brands and have come to hold
nearly a 90-percent share of the domestic market.
</P>
<P>
Changhong now has 38 percent of China's color TV market, and
has begun to venture into the world market.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 81 percent of the VCD products in China are made
by domestic manufacturers, and Chinese computers now have 60
percent of the market.
</P>
<P>
Electronics have grown at an average of 27.5 percent since
1992, and are now competitive in quality, and more and more in
price as well.
</P>
<P>
China has had rapid growth in integrated circuit production, an
important part of the sector, in the past few years, and the
country's first miniature integrated circuit assembly line is
now under construction.
</P>
<P>
However, industry analysts said that China's electronics
information industry still lags behind the developed countries,
especially in items like mobile phones.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
