<HEADLINE> Expression From Dante Popular On Chinese Campus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 18 (Xinhua) -- A study of a university in Shanghai
has found that nearly a third of the students there are using a
quote from the Italian poet Dante as a kind of motto.
</P>
<P>
The study at Fudan University, one of China's top universities,
of 489 students, found that 82 had chosen Dante's "Follow your own
path and don't worry about what others say" as their motto, out of
271 people who said they have a motto. This was followed by
"Believe yourself" and "self improvement without stop".
</P>
<P>
Students also expressed a common hope for greater understanding
and care and said they are always ready to give a hand to those in
need.
</P>
<P>
Some specialists think that mottos can play an important role
in children's growth and they say that a positive motto can help
children develop a better character. 
</P>
