<HEADLINE> Floods Threaten Port Along Lake Victoria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Port Bell pier at Luzira is likely
to be submerged by the rising water levels of Lake Victoria, an
official of the Directorate of Water Development at Entebbe has
warned.
</P>
<P>
Monday's New Vision newspaper quoted the official, who
declined to be named, as saying that Kampala-Port Bell railway
line was also threatened by the rising lake levels.
</P>
<P>
"The extension of Lake Victoria waters inland will affect
Nakivubo drainage system in Kampala to the extent that any amount
of rainfall will cause floods,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
The landing bay for Clovergem fish factory near Entebbe
international airport had already been submerged, he added.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper issued on May 7 said the flooding waters had
submerged 20 buildings at Gaba landing site, southeast of
Kampala. The water level in the lake was recorded at 12.30 meters
above zero datum, only 0.5 meters away from the highest water
level recorded 100 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The dock is the water gateway for Kampala and handles big
volumes of imports and exports. The pier connects Uganda's
railway system with those of Kenya and Tanzania using wagon
ferries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
