<HEADLINE> Northwest China City Developing Investment Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Lanzhou, capital of northwest
China's Gansu Province, improved its investment environment by
investing in the city's infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Major projects included the completion of two expressways to
alleviate auto traffic, electricity reconstruction of the
Lanzhou-Wuwei railway and an expansion of Zhongchuan Airport.
</P>
<P>
A city official said that Lanzhou also increased its investment
in posts and telecommunications. In 1997, Lanzhou accelerated the
installation of optical fiber lines between Xi'an, Lanzhou and
Urumqi, and between Lanzhou and Tibet.
</P>
<P>
At present, all districts and counties in Lanzhou have
program-controlled telephones. The telephone capacity in Lanzhou
has reached 442,000.
</P>
<P>
As part of the reconstruction program of the old city, Lanzhou
expanded more than 20 main roads in the city area, which totally
changed the traffic jam situation in the city.
</P>
<P>
Lanzhou built a gas plant with a daily production capacity of
540,000 cubic meters, and more than 400 kilometers of gas
pipes. Two sewage treatment factories were also built, with daily
treatment capacity of 116,000 cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
Plus, the city also put in 200 million yuan to plant trees and
grass, bringing the green coverage of Lanzhou to over 7,300
hectares. 
</P>
