<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Natural Gas Companies Fined for Monopoly Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Two natural gas suppliers in
southwest China's Sichuan Province have been fined 50,000 yuan and
150,000 yuan for illegal monopoly performance.
</P>
<P>
During a recent law-enforcement inspection, the capital's
industrial and commercial department found that the natural gas
supply company in Chongzhou city was conducting unfair competition
by forcing other gas businesses out of the market.
</P>
<P>
Applicants for gas supply had to buy gas stoves at the
company's shops or they would be charged extra service fees for
stoves they purchased elsewhere, officials said. As a result,
consumers' favorite choice, the Chengdu Qianfeng Geyser Factory,
had to give up its local sales outlet.
</P>
<P>
The natural gas supply company in Qionglai city was another
example. It had long been taking the advantage of its monopoly
status to force gas users into buying stoves at its shops,
officials said. What's more, it reportedly asked property
developers to pay for gas stoves and pipes in advance, and would
not provide gas to those who did not pay the fees in time.
</P>
<P>
Related department have issued a notice calling for fair
competition and a smooth market order.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
