<HEADLINE> China to Increase Use of Plastic Film for Agriculture in Arid Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 18 (Xinhua) -- China will spread the technique of
covering young wheat seedlings under plastic film to 530,300
hectares of land this year, 2.8 times the 1997 figure, according
to an official from the Department of Science and Technology under
the Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The technique will be mainly applied to arid areas in north and
northwest China, the official said today.
</P>
<P>
The use of plastic film is part of the "Harvest Program"
organized by the Ministry of Agriculture since 1987. It is aimed
at spreading practical agricultural techniques and getting a high
yield from main crops in large areas.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in 1997 the technique added to output by
220 million kilograms (kg). The average per-hectare yield
increased by 1,108 kg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
