<HEADLINE> Volvo A New Star In China's Auto Industry Constellation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Volvo's Sino-Swedish auto venture
produced 500 luxury buses over the past three years, accounting
for a third of the buses sold on the domestic market, "China
Business Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
The three-year-old joint venture had an output value of 580
million yuan (69.9 million US dollars) last year and wants to
increase that to one billion yuan (120 million US dollars) this
year.
</P>
<P>
Volvo has been successful in China since it sold its first 30
buses in June 1996. It later was designated as the major
transportation of the National People's Congress and the World
Women's Conference and several other national or international
conferences.
</P>
<P>
Because more expressways have opened over recent years, the
company wants to expand its annual production capacity of large or
medium-sized buses to 1,500 by the year 2000. 
