<HEADLINE> China's Largest Wind-Power Center Built in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 18 (Xinhua) -- A wind-power center with a
generating capacity of 63,600 kilowatts (kw) has passed the state
technical assessment, the overseas edition of "People's Daily"
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The center lies in Dabancheng, in northwest China's Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region and cost 500 million yuan to complete.
</P>
<P>
At present, more than 200 power-generating units are in
operation at the center. Another 20 sets of 600-kw units and 51
500-kw units will be installed later this year, bringing an
expected added capacity of 37,500 kw by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The generating capacity of the center makes up one-third of the
total installed wind power capacity in the country, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang, the largest inland province-level area in China, has
nine wind zones covering a combined area of 150,000 square
kilometers. The total generating capacity in the zones is
estimated at 80 million kw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
