<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Bank to Receive Money for Rural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Cash-strapped Thai farmers are
likely to obtain loans at an affordable rate from the Bank for
Agriculture and Agricultural Cooperative in the near future, as
the bank is to receive 10 billion baht (263 million U.S. dollars)
low-interest loans.
</P>
<P>
The Bangkok Post Monday quoted Deputy Finance Minister Pitchout
Phanvichartkul as saying that the money would come from the
government's 5 billion dollar global bond issue.
</P>
<P>
Projects eligible for loans include shops in rural communities,
processing and production of agricultural products, and planned
central agricultural markets.
</P>
<P>
Last Tuesday, the cabinet approved law changes, allowing
low-interest loans for the above mentioned purposes. The changes
are waiting for the consideration of the parliament next month.
</P>
<P>
The Bank for Agriculture and Agricultural Cooperative obtains
financial support from various sources such as the World Bank. But
the 11 percent interest rate makes it impossible for the bank to
relend money to farmers at rates which they can afford.
</P>
<P>
But if the bank could obtain funds at 8 to 9 percent, it can
pass on the benefits to farmers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
