<HEADLINE> Iridium's Last Five of 66-Satellites Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The last five of the 66
communication satellites from Iridium were launched into Earth's
low orbit Sunday from Vandenberg Air Force Base on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The launch is the ninth scheduled Delta launch at Vandenberg
Air Force Base in California, but also the 15th Iridium System
launch in just 12 months, which will bring the total number of
operational satellites on orbit to 67.
</P>
<P>
China's Long March rocket in less than five months send six of
Iridium's satellites into space.
</P>
<P>
With Sunday's launch, Iridium System will on schedule provide a
worldwide digital telephone network in September. The
5-billion-dollar Iridium System plans to offer full global
communications coverage and a variety of communications
services, including voice, data, fax and paging to customers with
Iridium handheld telephones and pagers.
</P>
<P>
"We have achieved one of the critical milestones necessary to
provide the first truly global, hand-held wireless phone service,"
said Edward F. Staiano, vice chairman and CEO of Iridium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980518.0263 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dhaka Committed to Protecting Children's Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dhaka, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh has been committed to
protecting the rights of children, The Independent daily reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
This was stated by Mozammel Hossain, state minister for women
and children affairs and social welfare, while inaugurating a
workshop on promoting good practices in implementing the
Convention on the Rights of the Child (CRC) in Dhaka Sunday.
</P>
<P>
As one of the first countries to sign and ratify the CRC
adopted by the United Nations in 1990, Bangladesh had been taking
necessary steps to ensure the rights of children since then, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The government had adopted a National Children's Policy
intended to ensure security and development of children in line
with the provisions of the convention, he said.
</P>
<P>
Following the ratification of the CRC, the former Ministry of
Women Affairs was renamed as the Ministry of Women and Children
Affairs in 1994 which, he said, reflected the commitment of the
government to children's development.
</P>
<P>
The CRC has been translated into Bengali and 500,000 printed
copies of the convention were being distributed among teachers of
primary schools, mother clubs, children organizations, government
officials, as well as the media to promote awareness of the rights
children enunciated in the document, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
