<HEADLINE> Inner Mongolia Using Japanese Loans to Improve Urban Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, May 18 (Xinhua) -- North China's Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region has launched five projects using Japanese loans
since late 1997 to improve its cities, according to a regional
government official.
</P>
<P>
The official says that the region will launch 16 more similar
projects this year, according to a local official.
</P>
<P>
He says that the 21 projects will need 2.45 billion yuan, part
of which will come from 15.2 billion Japanese yen (947 million
yuan) in 30-year loans.
</P>
<P>
