<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Crime in U.S. Keeps Dropping, Says FBI </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Serious crimes reported to the
police in 1997 in the United States declined for a sixth
consecutive year, with reductions in every region, the FBI said.
</P>
<P>
However, Attorney General Janet Reno warned against
overconfidence, saying new problems always are possible.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary figures released Sunday reflected a cumulative four
percent decrease in seven major crimes recorded by 9,582 police
agencies around the nation.
</P>
<P>
The violent crimes of murder, rape, robbery and aggravated
assault dropped five percent nationally. Far more numerous
property crimes of burglary, auto theft and larceny-theft dipped
four percent.
</P>
<P>
The most dramatic declines were in murder, for which statistics
are the most reliable and uniform. Homicide was down nine percent
nationwide but 14 percent in cities of 250,000 to 500,000; 11 per
cent in cities over one million and in suburban counties; and 10
percent in cities of 500,000 to one million people.
</P>
<P>
"We can never relax our vigilance about crime, about
enforcement, about prevention," Reno said, because "there's going
to be a new problem down the road." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980518.0304 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Silicon Valley Remains Hot Place for Venture Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Silicon Valley absorbed 830
million U.S. dollars of venture capital in the first quarter of
this year, 48 percent more than the corresponding period last
year.
</P>
<P>
The money went to 156 companies in the 50-mile-long stretch of
real estate south of San Francisco, according to a survey
published Saturday by the consulting firm Price Waterhouse.
</P>
<P>
The survey found that the average investment was 5.3 million
dollars, an increase of 39 percent over the first quarter last
year.
</P>
<P>
Software, telecommunications and net-related companies
continued to top the list, respectively accounting for 31 percent,
25 percent and 16 percent of the total investment.
</P>
<P>
In the United States, venture capitalists invested 3.6 billion
dollars in the first quarter. Silicon Valley took away 23 percent
of the national total.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-two companies in Silicon Valley received funding of 10
million dollars or more. They raised 39 percent of the venture
capital invested in the area. A year ago, only 10 companies
received such large amounts. Typically, the money went to
companies that already have a product and can demonstrate revenue.
The single largest investment, 33 million dollars, went to a
company producing the architecture to enable two-way data
communication through cellular phones and other wireless devices.
</P>
<P>
Home to 7,000 electronic and software firms, Silicon Valley has
been in the midst of a production and employment boom that places
it in the forefront of the U.S. economy. Santa Clara County in
California, where Silicon Valley is located, now leads the United
States in exports, outpacing New York and Detroit and making up
five percent of the U.S. total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
